Nice!<br/><br/>This was written by a guy... it's pretty damn smart. Girls -- Have a sense of humor! 
<br /><br />I never quite figured out why the sexual urge of men and women differ so much. And I never have figured out the whole Venus and Mars thing. I have never figured out why men think with their head and women with their heart. 
<br /><br />FOR EXAMPLE: 
<br /><br />One evening last week, my girlfriend and I were getting into bed. 
<br /><br />Well, the passion starts to heat up, and she eventually says, &quot;I don't feel like it, I just want you to hold me.&quot; 
<br /><br />I said, &quot;WHAT??!! What was that?!&quot; 
<br /><br />So she says the words that every boyfriend on the planet dreads to hear... 
<br /><br />&quot;You're just not in touch with my emotional needs as a woman enough for me to satisfy your physical needs as a man.&quot; 
<br /><br />She responded to my puzzled look by saying, &quot;Can't you just love me for who I am and not what I do for you in the bedroom?&quot; 
<br /><br />Realizing that nothing was going to happen that night, I went to sleep. 
<br /><br />The very next day I opted to take the day off of work to spend time with her. We went out to a nice lunch and then went shopping at a big, big unnamed department store. I walked around with her while she tried on several different very expensive outfits. She couldn't decide which one to take, so I told her we'd just buy them all. She wanted new shoes to compliment her new clothes, so I said, &quot;Lets get a pair for each outfit.&quot; 
<br /><br />We went on to the jewelry department where she picked out a pair of diamond earrings. Let me tell you... she was so excited. She must have thought I was one wave short of a shipwreck. I started to think she was testing me because she asked for a tennis bracelet when she doesn't even know how to play tennis. 
<br /><br />I think I threw her for a loop when I said, &quot;That's fine, honey.&quot; She was almost nearing sexual satisfaction from all of the excitement. Smiling with excited anticipation, she finally said, &quot;I think this is all 
<br />dear, let's go to the cashier.&quot; 
<br /><br />I could hardly contain myself when I blurted out, &quot;No honey, I don't feel like it.&quot; 
<br /><br />Her face just went completely blank as her jaw dropped with a baffled, &quot;WHAT?&quot; 
<br /><br />I then said, &quot;Honey! I just want you to HOLD this stuff for a while. You're just not in touch with my financial needs as a man enough for me to satisfy your shopping needs as a woman.&quot; 
<br /><br />And just when she had this look like she was going to kill me, I added, &quot;Why can't you just love me for who I am and not for the things I buy you?&quot; 
<br /><br />Apparently I'm not having sex tonight either....but at least that bitch knows I'm smarter than her. 
<br /><br />Just repost this to get a laugh... we know someones going through this sought of a drought, hopefully it gets to them.

A name. Written by me<br/><br/>Alex sat in his room,  thinking. They weren't any particular thoughts , just ideas and feelings floating around in spirals. Phone numbers, prices of things he wanted to buy , favourite bands and..... her. Alex smiled, glad he had something of meaning to think about. In his mind he saw her smile and a small gasp escaped his lips and his heart throbbed with longing. He loved her, even if she didn't know it. He had the perfect way to tell her , a song , written purely out of his heart and intended for only her to hear. Alex picked up his guitar and strummed a few chords then pulled out a battered tape recorder and set it on the floor and began to play, singing and playing the song that he had written for her. Then a wave of sadness swept over him. He didn't know her name. But he was going to change that.
<br /><br />Alex rumbled along the road , sitting alone on the bus as usual watching the houses pass by and the road being swallowed by the buses tyres. She sat up the front talking to her friend, she looked sad and concerned about something. As Alex looked on , her heard their conversation drift towards him.
<br />&quot;Why are you moving ?&quot;
<br />&quot;Don't know, parents want to , they hate it here&quot;
<br />&quot;But why? I'm going to miss you so much&quot;
<br />&quot;Don't worry, we will keep in touch&quot;
<br />&quot;But won't you miss him? Alex?&quot;
<br />&quot;Yes I will , I just wish he would talk to me, I love him&quot;
<br /><br />All at the same time , Alex smiled and felt his heart burst, a mosaic, a dance of broken gleaming fragments. She loved him , but she was moving. Alex couldn't remember being more happy and sad at the same time. Alex knew what he had to do to make her see he loved her too.
<br /><br />That night , Alex took his guitar to her house and found her bedroom window and sat on the lawn and began to play. His voice soared and lights began to flick on in the house and voices coudl be heard. Then her window opened and she appeared, tears coursing silently down her cheeks. He finished his song and walked over to her, pulling her close for a kiss that was only brief, but would be locked away in his heart forever, she leant in and whispered in his ear something he would remember forever, even when he grew old. Then her father appeared and Alex took one last look vefore melting into the night.
<br /><br />Alex never saw her again. People at school said she moved away the day after he sang to her. Alex missed her but with each day that passed it grew a little easier. Alex eventually sold his guitar and gave up his song writing, he didn't need it anymore, he'd achieved what he wanted and was happy with it. Alex grew up and met someone else, they married, had 2 kids and eventually divorced. It wasn't the happiest of endings, nor was it the saddest. Because Alex was content with it all, because he had a memory of a girl whispering in his ear something he would never forget. 
<br /><br />A name.
<br /><br />Annie.
<br /><br />THE END &lt;3
